claim.claim-text:
1. A semiconductor integrated circuit device comprising: 
(a) a semiconductor substrate having at its principal surface a first area and a second area planarly surrounded by the first area; 
(b) a first insulative film formed over the principal surface of the semiconductor substrate in the second area; 
(c) a conductor piece formed over the first insulative film; 
(d) a semiconductor region formed at the semiconductor substrate principal surface on both sides of the conductor piece; and 
(e) an oxide film being formed at the semiconductor substrate principal surface in the first area and having a film thickness greater than that of the first insulative film, 
wherein nitrogen is introduced at a surface portion of the oxide film.

7. A semiconductor integrated circuit device comprising: 
(a) a semiconductor substrate having at its principal surface a first area, a second area and a third area, the second and third areas being planarly surrounded by the first area; 
(b) a first insulative film formed above the semiconductor substrate principal surface in the second area; 
(c) a second insulative film being formed over the semiconductor substrate principal surface in the third area and being less in film thickness than the first insulative film; 
(d) a first conductor piece formed over the first insulative film; 
(e) a second conductor piece formed over the second insulative film; 
(f) a first semiconductor region formed at the semiconductor substrate principal surface on both sides of the first conductor piece in the second area; 
(g) a second semiconductor region formed at the semiconductor substrate principal surface on both sides of the second conductor piece in the third area; and 
(h) an oxide film being formed at the semiconductor substrate principal surface in the first area and being greater in film thickness than the first and second insulative films, 
wherein nitrogen is introduced at a surface portion of the oxide film.

15. A method of fabricating a semiconductor integrated circuit device, comprising: 
(a) exposing a first area of a semiconductor substrate principal surface to thereby selectively form a first insulative film at the semiconductor substrate principal surface in a second area as surrounded by the first area; 
(b) forming a groove in the semiconductor substrate surface in the first area; 
(c) forming a second insulative film within the groove and over the first insulative film in such a way as to bury the groove; 
(d) applying polishing to the second insulative film to thereby permit the second insulative film to selectively remain within the groove; 
(e) introducing nitrogen into the second insulative film within the groove; 
(f) removing the first insulative film of the second area; 
(g) forming a third insulative film at the semiconductor substrate surface in the second area; 
(h) forming a conductor piece over the third insulative film; and 
(i) introducing in the second area an impurity into the semiconductor substrate surface on both sides of the conductor piece.

20. A method of fabricating a semiconductor integrated circuit device, comprising: 
(a) exposing a first area of a semiconductor substrate principal surface to thereby selectively form a silicon nitride film at the semiconductor substrate principal surface in a second area; 
(b) forming a groove in the semiconductor substrate surface in the first area; 
(c) forming a first silicon oxide film within the groove to bury the groove; 
(d) introducing nitrogen into the first silicon oxide film within the groove; 
(e) removing the silicon nitride film in the second area; 
(f) forming a second silicon oxide film at the semiconductor substrate surface in the second area; 
(g) forming a conductor piece over the second silicon oxide film; and 
(h) introducing an impurity into the semiconductor substrate surface on both sides of the conductor piece in the second area.

21. A method of fabricating a semiconductor integrated circuit device, comprising: 
(a) exposing a first area of a semiconductor substrate principal surface to thereby selectively form a first insulative film at the semiconductor substrate principal surface in a second area as surrounded by the first area; 
(b) forming a groove in the semiconductor substrate surface in the first area; 
(c) forming a second insulative film within the groove and over the first insulative film to bury the groove; 
(d) applying polishing to the second insulative film to thereby permit the second insulative film to selectively remain within the groove; 
(e) introducing nitrogen by an ion implantation method into the second insulative film within the groove; 
(f) removing the first insulative film in the second area; 
(g) forming a third insulative film at the semiconductor substrate surface in the second area with the first insulative film removed away; 
(h) forming a conductor piece over the third insulative film; and 
(i) introducing in the second area an impurity into the semiconductor substrate surface on both sides of the conductor piece.

23. A method of fabricating a semiconductor integrated circuit device, comprising: 
(a) exposing a first area of a semiconductor substrate principal surface to thereby selectively form a first insulative film at the semiconductor substrate principal surface in a second area and a third area, the second and third areas being surrounded by the first area; 
(b) forming a groove in the semiconductor substrate surface of the first area; 
(c) forming a second insulative film within the groove and over the first insulative film to bury the groove; 
(d) polishing the second insulative film to permit the second insulative film to selectively remain within the groove; 
(e) introducing nitrogen into the second insulative film in the first area; 
(f) removing the first insulative film in the second and third areas; 
(g) forming a third insulative film at the semiconductor substrate surface in the second and third areas; 
(h) selectively removing the third insulative film in the third area while letting the third insulative film remain in the second area; 
(i) applying thermal processing to the semiconductor substrate in an oxygen atmosphere to thereby form a fourth insulative film at the semiconductor substrate surface of the second area while forming at the semiconductor substrate surface of the third area a fifth insulative film less in thickness than the fourth insulative film; 
(j) forming a first conductor piece over the fourth insulative film and a second conductive piece over the fifth insulative film; and 
(k) introducing in the second area an impurity into the semiconductor substrate surface on both sides of the first conductor piece while introducing in the third area an impurity into the semiconductor substrate surface on both sides of the second conductor piece.

24. A method of fabricating a semiconductor integrated circuit device, comprising: 
(a) exposing a first area of a semiconductor substrate principal surface to thereby selectively form a first insulative film at the semiconductor substrate principal surface in a second area and a third area, the second and third areas being surrounded by the first area; 
(b) forming a groove in the semiconductor substrate surface of the first area; 
(c) forming a second insulative film within the groove and over the first insulative film to bury the groove; 
(d) polishing the second insulative film to permit the second insulative film to selectively remain within the groove; 
(e) introducing nitrogen into the second insulative film within the groove; 
(f) forming a third insulative film at the semiconductor substrate surface in the second third areas; 
(g) selectively removing the third insulative film in the third area while letting the third insulative film be left in the second area; 
(h) applying thermal processing to the semiconductor substrate in an oxygen atmosphere to thereby form a fourth insulative film at the semiconductor substrate surface of the second area while forming at the semiconductor substrate surface of the third area a fifth insulative film less in thickness than the fourth insulative film; 
(i) forming a first conductor piece over the fourth insulative film and a second conductive piece over the fifth insulative film; and 
(j) introducing in the second area an impurity into the semiconductor substrate surface on both sides of the first conductor piece while introducing in the third area an impurity into the semiconductor substrate surface on both sides of the second conductor piece.

25. A method of fabricating a semiconductor integrated circuit device, comprising: 
(a) exposing a first area of a semiconductor substrate principal surface to thereby selectively form a first insulative film at the semiconductor substrate principal surface in a second area and a third area, the second and third areas being surrounded by the first area; 
(b) forming a groove in the semiconductor substrate surface of the first area; 
(c) forming a second insulative film within the groove and over the first insulative film to bury the groove; 
(d) polishing the second insulative film to permit the second insulative film to selectively remain within the groove; 
(e) introducing nitrogen into the semiconductor substrate surface in the third area; 
(f) removing the first insulative film in the second area and the third area; 
(g) thermally processing the semiconductor substrate surface with the first insulative film removed therefrom in an oxygen atmosphere to thereby form a third insulative film at the semiconductor substrate surface in the second area while forming at the semiconductor substrate surface of the third area a fourth insulative film being less in thickness than the third insulative film; 
(h) forming a first conductor piece over the third insulative film and a second conductive piece over the fourth insulative film; and 
(i) introducing in the second area an impurity into the semiconductor substrate surface on both sides of the first conductor piece while introducing in the third area an impurity into the semiconductor substrate surface on both sides of the second conductor piece.

26. A method of fabricating a semiconductor integrated circuit device, comprising: 
(a) exposing a first area of a semiconductor substrate principal surface to thereby selectively form a first insulative film at the semiconductor substrate principal surface in a second area and a third area, the second and third areas being surrounded by the first area; 
(b) forming a groove in the semiconductor substrate surface of the first area; 
(c) forming a second insulative film within the groove and over the first insulative film to bury the groove; 
(d) polishing the second insulative film to permit the second insulative film to selectively remain within the groove; 
(e) introducing nitrogen into the second insulative film in the first area; 
(f) introducing nitrogen into the semiconductor substrate surface of the third area; 
(g) removing the first insulative film of the second and third areas; 
(h) thermally processing the semiconductor substrate in an oxygen atmosphere to thereby form a third insulative film at the semiconductor substrate surface of the second area while forming at the semiconductor substrate surface of the third area a fourth insulative film being less in thickness than the third insulative film; 
(i) forming a first conductor piece over the third insulative film and a second conductive piece over the fourth insulative film; and 
(j) introducing in the second area an impurity into the semiconductor substrate surface on both sides of the first conductor piece while introducing in the third area an impurity into the semiconductor substrate surface on both sides of the second conductor piece.

27. A method of fabricating a semiconductor integrated circuit device, comprising: 
(a) exposing a first area of a semiconductor substrate principal surface to thereby selectively form a first insulative film at the semiconductor substrate principal surface of a second area as surrounded by the first area; 
(b) forming a groove in the semiconductor substrate surface of the first area; 
(c) forming a second insulative film within the groove and over the first insulative film to bury the groove; 
(d) polishing the second insulative film to cause the second insulative film to selectively remain within the groove; 
(e) etching the second insulative film thereby letting a surface of the second insulative film be lower than a surface of the first insulative film; 
(f) forming a third insulative film over the first and second insulative films; 
(g) introducing nitrogen into the second insulative film in the first area through the third insulative film; 
(h) removing the first and third insulative films of the second area; 
(i) forming a fourth insulative film at the semiconductor substrate surface of the second area; 
(j) forming a conductor piece over the fourth insulative film of the second area; and 
(k) introducing in the second area an impurity into the semiconductor substrate surface on both sides of the conductor piece.

29. A method of fabricating a semiconductor integrated circuit device, comprising: 
(a) exposing a first area of a semiconductor substrate principal surface to thereby selectively form a first insulative film at the semiconductor substrate principal surface of a second area surrounded by the first area; 
(b) forming a groove in the semiconductor substrate surface of the first area; 
(c) thermally processing the semiconductor substrate in a nitrogen-containing atmosphere; 
(d) forming a second insulative film within the groove and over the first insulative film to bury the groove; 
(e) polishing the second insulative film to permit the second insulative film to be left selectively in the first area; 
(f) introducing nitrogen into the second insulative film of the first area; 
(g) forming a third insulative film at the semiconductor substrate surface of the second area with the first insulative film removed away therefrom; 
(h) forming a conductor piece over the third insulative film; and 
(i) introducing in the second area an impurity into the semiconductor substrate surface on both sides of the conductor piece.

31. A method of fabricating a semiconductor integrated circuit device, comprising: 
(a) exposing a first area of a semiconductor substrate principal surface to selectively form a first nitride film over the semiconductor substrate principal surface of a second area surrounded by the first area; 
(b) forming a groove in the semiconductor substrate surface of the first area; 
(c) forming a first oxide film at a surface of the groove; 
(d) forming a second nitride film over the first oxide film; 
(e) forming a second oxide film within the groove and over the first nitride film to bury the groove; 
(f) polishing the second oxide film to cause the second oxide film to be selectively left in the first area; 
(g) introducing nitrogen into the second oxide film of the first area; 
(h) forming a third oxide film at the semiconductor substrate surface of the second area with the first and second nitride films removed away therefrom; 
(i) forming a conductor piece over the third oxide film; and 
(j) introducing in the second area an impurity into the semiconductor substrate surface on both sides of the conductor piece.

33. A method of fabricating a semiconductor integrated circuit device, comprising: 
(a) exposing a first area of a semiconductor substrate principal surface to selectively form a first insulative film at the semiconductor substrate principal surface of a second area as surrounded by the first area; 
(b) forming a groove in the semiconductor substrate surface of the first area; 
(c) forming a second insulative film within the groove and over the first insulative film to bury the groove; 
(d) polishing the second insulative film to let the second insulative film selectively remain within the groove; 
(e) doping nitrogen and silicon into the second insulative film within the groove; 
(f) removing the first insulative film of the second area; 
(g) forming a third insulative film at the semiconductor substrate surface of the second area; 
(h) forming a conductor piece over the third insulative film; and 
(i) doping in the second area an impurity into the semiconductor substrate surface on both sides of the conductor piece.
